New rules governing black ownership of South Africa’s mining industry will be completed “very soon,” President Cyril Ramaphosa said at a Japan-Africa trade forum in Johannesburg. “The Mining Charter will be finalised very soon and we have set a deadline,” Ramaphosa said, without giving details of the timing. Africa’s most-industrialised country will try to remove “blockages” to investment in a bid to attract as much as $100 billion over the next five years, he said.